Backend Readme
Description
This repository contains the backend code for the Job Board application. The backend is implemented with ExpressJS, MongoDB, and Mongoose, providing RESTful API endpoints for user authentication, job listings, and applications.
Frontend Repository:https://github.com/JOB-FINDR/job-findr-frontend 

Instructions to Run this App Locally:
1- Clone the Repository:
git clone <backend-repo-url>


2- Install Dependencies:
npm install

3- Environment Variables:
Create a.env file in the root of the frontend directory.

4- Run the Application:
npm run dev


Demo
Visit https://job-findr-api.adaptable.app  to test the API.

